1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:28,450
♪Like a flock of birds
pressing ever forward♪

2
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:33,350
♪Stranded on an island
shrouded in heavy mist♪

3
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:38,410
♪We may seem small
beneath the vast world♪

4
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:43,680
♪But not once have we felt despair♪

5
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,770
♪We've crossed waves
a thousand layers deep♪

6
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,530
♪Stepped on reefs hidden in the dark♪

7
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:54,730
♪Facing sharper winds head-on♪

8
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:57,660
♪Our wounds now stitched
into battle robes♪

9
00:00:57,660 --> 00:01:00,370
♪The long night
is branded by starlight♪

10
00:01:00,370 --> 00:01:05,440
♪We embrace this deep blue together♪

11
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:10,620
♪At the edge of the vast unknown,
I remain unchanged♪

12
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:16,540
♪Holding fast with lonely courage,
roaring without fear♪

13
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:21,850
♪Determined to be
both my friend and my rival♪

14
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:27,030
♪No one dares to blindly
urge me to turn back♪

15
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:32,090
♪I choose what I believe is worth it♪

16
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:38,340
=Rose and Gun=

17
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 12=

18
00:01:52,770 --> 00:01:55,090
Don't eat that, Honey.
It must taste awful.

19
00:01:55,290 --> 00:01:56,610
Let's just order takeout.

20
00:01:57,010 --> 00:01:57,770
Not at all.

21
00:01:58,090 --> 00:01:59,350
My wife cooked this herself.

22
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:00,582
How can I say it tastes bad?

23
00:02:00,650 --> 00:02:01,770
I'll eat all of it.

24
00:02:02,770 --> 00:02:04,610
Order whatever you want for yourself.

25
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:09,170
Seriously, stop. Let's just go out.

26
00:02:09,890 --> 00:02:11,300
What about all this food then?

27
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,493
It would be such a waste.

28
00:02:13,450 --> 00:02:15,840
You've never done any survival training.

29
00:02:16,130 --> 00:02:18,290
Food is precious.

30
00:02:19,493 --> 00:02:20,860
Fine, I'll eat it with you.

31
00:02:29,490 --> 00:02:30,410
I mean,

32
00:02:30,890 --> 00:02:33,450
it is a little bit bitter.

33
00:02:40,810 --> 00:02:41,570
Is it good?

34
00:02:42,490 --> 00:02:43,537
Yeah. It's good.

35
00:02:50,610 --> 00:02:51,410
Dear,

36
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:53,730
I feel like

37
00:02:54,650 --> 00:02:57,130
I aged two years
just by putting on this ring.

38
00:02:58,090 --> 00:02:59,650
No way. I don't see that.

39
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,650
My Zong looks good no matter what.

40
00:03:03,890 --> 00:03:05,060
I think so too.

41
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:07,130
Shameless.

42
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:14,490
Honey,

43
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:17,850
do you have any plans

44
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:19,000
for our honeymoon?

45
00:03:20,850 --> 00:03:21,400
I do.

46
00:03:23,930 --> 00:03:26,290
However you want to spend it,
that's how we'll do it.

47
00:03:27,890 --> 00:03:29,880
Can't you have
your own opinion for once?

48
00:03:30,130 --> 00:03:32,370
With this block of wood for a brain?

49
00:03:32,893 --> 00:03:33,970
I'll just listen to you.

50
00:03:33,970 --> 00:03:35,770
Wherever you want to go, we'll go.

51
00:03:37,730 --> 00:03:38,950
I knew you'd say that.

52
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:40,890
Good thing I came prepared.

53
00:03:43,810 --> 00:03:44,290
Look.

54
00:03:45,340 --> 00:03:46,700
Hangzhou, Xi'an, and Dali.

55
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:48,410
Lhasa could work too.

56
00:03:48,490 --> 00:03:50,450
Just the two of us. How does that sound?

57
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,030
Dear.

58
00:03:54,730 --> 00:03:56,090
You're getting carried away.

59
00:03:56,090 --> 00:03:57,320
Let's pick somewhere closer.

60
00:03:57,450 --> 00:03:58,190
Why?

61
00:03:59,330 --> 00:04:00,140
Think about it.

62
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:03,130
What if we're halfway through the trip,

63
00:04:03,130 --> 00:04:04,720
and I suddenly get called back to base?

64
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:07,110
That'd be so awkward.

65
00:04:10,010 --> 00:04:11,690
Nothing works for you.

66
00:04:11,690 --> 00:04:13,400
Plan it yourself. I'm out.

67
00:04:19,450 --> 00:04:19,970
I've got it.

68
00:04:20,690 --> 00:04:21,820
Don't worry, Honey.

69
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:23,940
I'll come up

70
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:27,070
with the perfect
honeymoon itinerary for you.

71
00:04:50,610 --> 00:04:52,000
If you aim too long,

72
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,204
you're more likely to miss.

73
00:04:53,330 --> 00:04:53,860
Got it?

74
00:04:54,890 --> 00:04:55,390
Got it.

75
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:56,970
You sure you got it?

76
00:04:59,450 --> 00:05:00,890
Captain Tang just called.

77
00:05:00,982 --> 00:05:02,250
He wants to speak to you.

78
00:05:02,930 --> 00:05:04,390
Call him back after training.

79
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:46,380
(Wu Si)

80
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:03,290
The number you're calling
is currently unavailable.

81
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,170
Please try again later.

82
00:06:05,170 --> 00:06:06,810
Sorry. The number you have dialed...

83
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,980
("New Perspective"
Disaster Response Report)

84
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:33,980
(and Second-Half Work Plan,
presented by Tang Xin)

85
00:06:33,980 --> 00:06:35,820
(Wu Si: Are you asleep?
If not, let's talk.)

86
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:38,404
(I've thought about the question
you asked me at the Mazhan Town.)

87
00:06:41,020 --> 00:06:46,900
(I want to see you.)

88
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:52,700
(Notifications muted)

89
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:21,330
Zong Qing!

90
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:26,050
This isn't a field drill.

91
00:07:26,650 --> 00:07:28,280
Can you slow down?

92
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:31,070
You're the one who overslept.

93
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:32,640
We agreed to head out by 6 AM.

94
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,160
Any slower and we'll miss everything.

95
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:36,970
Miss what? We're on our honeymoon,

96
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:39,710
not rushing to a morning market.

97
00:07:39,893 --> 00:07:41,004
Sorry, force of habit.

98
00:07:42,850 --> 00:07:43,780
I'm tired.

99
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:47,410
We're almost at the top.

100
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,582
Just a few more steps.
The view is amazing up there.

101
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:50,580
Come on!

102
00:07:51,890 --> 00:07:52,350
No.

103
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:53,320
How about

104
00:07:53,930 --> 00:07:55,680
I sing something to hype you up?

105
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:57,400
Ready? Go!

106
00:07:57,810 --> 00:08:01,200
♪The red flag flutters in the wind♪

107
00:08:01,470 --> 00:08:03,093
♪Our song is loud♪

108
00:08:03,093 --> 00:08:04,410
Zong Qing, this is our honeymoon!

109
00:08:04,410 --> 00:08:05,910
Can't you sing something romantic?

110
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:08,850
What even is this place?
Just mountains and wilderness.

111
00:08:09,370 --> 00:08:10,410
Don't say that.

112
00:08:11,090 --> 00:08:12,870
I came here
during a training exercise once.

113
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:14,770
It used to be way wilder back then.

114
00:08:15,026 --> 00:08:16,050
Just forests everywhere.

115
00:08:16,770 --> 00:08:17,390
Also,

116
00:08:17,850 --> 00:08:19,160
if you ever get lost in the woods,

117
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,260
carve something

118
00:08:20,670 --> 00:08:22,170
into the trees.

119
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,450
I'm not getting lost. Who'd get lost?

120
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:27,160
Right. You're the smartest.

121
00:08:27,530 --> 00:08:27,870
Come on.

122
00:08:28,570 --> 00:08:29,050
Look.

123
00:08:29,170 --> 00:08:30,760
There's a waterfall up ahead! Hurry!

124
00:08:32,370 --> 00:08:33,290
You see it?

125
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:35,530
Wow, there really is a waterfall!

126
00:08:35,530 --> 00:08:37,560
What do you mean "really"?
I'd never lie to you.

127
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:44,970
Three, two, one, cheese!

128
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:45,810
Cheese!

129
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:47,130
Got it.

130
00:08:47,671 --> 00:08:49,071
Come on! Let's take a selfie!

131
00:08:49,330 --> 00:08:49,680
Okay.

132
00:08:52,315 --> 00:08:53,048
Here we go.

133
00:08:55,010 --> 00:08:56,270
Three, two, one.

134
00:08:57,650 --> 00:08:58,270
One more.

135
00:09:02,337 --> 00:09:03,550
Pay attention to the technique.

136
00:09:20,010 --> 00:09:20,620
Yi Nanwang.

137
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:21,250
Here.

138
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,640
Forgot the basics?

139
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:23,630
Sir.

140
00:09:23,870 --> 00:09:24,790
For some reason,

141
00:09:24,915 --> 00:09:26,350
the gun just won't cooperate today.

142
00:09:26,810 --> 00:09:28,010
Then feed it.

143
00:09:28,210 --> 00:09:29,360
It's a starving beast.

144
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:30,810
You need to feed it bullets

145
00:09:30,810 --> 00:09:32,380
that weigh 10, 20 times more than you.

146
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,140
(People's Liberation Army Navy)

147
00:09:36,115 --> 00:09:36,760
Sergeant Cheng.

148
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:39,130
He's been overworked.

149
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:41,290
He never got a break in the Mazhan Town.

150
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:45,610
Yi Nanwang.

151
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:46,110
Here.

152
00:09:46,110 --> 00:09:47,248
Inspect your weapon. Stand up.

153
00:09:47,271 --> 00:09:47,671
Yes, Sir.

154
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:56,590
Return your firearm.

155
00:09:57,004 --> 00:09:58,160
Head to the infirmary.

156
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:01,710
Come on.

157
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:04,620
You've got this.

158
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,320
- Honey, I can't walk anymore.
- Keep going.

159
00:10:08,537 --> 00:10:09,790
We're almost there. Come on.

160
00:10:18,382 --> 00:10:19,010
Push yourself.

161
00:10:19,737 --> 00:10:20,740
I can't go on, Honey...

162
00:10:22,010 --> 00:10:23,610
There are still so many steps...

163
00:10:23,610 --> 00:10:25,179
I can't go any further. I'm exhausted.

164
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:26,140
Just hold on a bit longer.

165
00:10:26,140 --> 00:10:27,410
The view up top is even better.

166
00:10:27,410 --> 00:10:29,050
No, I can't.

167
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:30,080
Just a bit more.

168
00:10:30,490 --> 00:10:31,350
No!

169
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:32,900
Then what do you want to do?

170
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:36,630
I want to find a homestay

171
00:10:36,810 --> 00:10:38,320
and crash in a bed.

172
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:41,380
Honey, this is a hiking trip.

173
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:43,090
Yes,

174
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:45,320
but it's also our honeymoon!

175
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:47,410
It's not military training.

176
00:10:47,570 --> 00:10:48,640
Let's go find a homestay

177
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:49,740
and just rest, please?

178
00:10:50,210 --> 00:10:51,560
Please.

179
00:10:52,010 --> 00:10:52,480
No.

180
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:55,420
Please, Honey.

181
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,710
Come on. Please?

182
00:10:56,710 --> 00:10:58,330
Please...

183
00:10:58,330 --> 00:11:00,330
- Okay, okay.
- Pretty please...

184
00:11:01,915 --> 00:11:02,960
Hurry up and find one.

185
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:08,330
A homestay, right?

186
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:13,810
Does it hurt here?

187
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:14,280
No.

188
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,030
Here?

189
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:17,970
No.

190
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:20,410
Be honest.

191
00:11:23,210 --> 00:11:23,740
Does it hurt?

192
00:11:23,970 --> 00:11:24,360
Yes.

193
00:11:27,626 --> 00:11:30,026
I'll give you some medicine
to help with circulation first.

194
00:11:30,071 --> 00:11:32,337
Take it easy and stay warm
these next couple of days.

195
00:11:32,730 --> 00:11:34,750
Avoid putting strain on your arm.

196
00:11:35,137 --> 00:11:36,760
You'll need three to five days of rest.

197
00:11:37,210 --> 00:11:38,070
Three to five days?

198
00:11:38,530 --> 00:11:39,660
But I still have training.

199
00:11:40,493 --> 00:11:42,000
Do you want your arm to fall off?

200
00:11:42,004 --> 00:11:43,810
Didn't you hear?
A few of the female soldiers

201
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:45,640
who went to Mazhan Town ignored the pain

202
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:47,204
and ended up with full-on tendonitis.

203
00:11:48,090 --> 00:11:48,690
Are they

204
00:11:49,730 --> 00:11:50,840
our female soldiers?

205
00:11:51,915 --> 00:11:52,826
What are their names?

206
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:54,670
Why are you so worked up?

207
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:58,248
Sergeant Cheng's girlfriend works
in our staff department.

208
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,990
They've been out of contact for days.

209
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:05,130
You have a girlfriend?

210
00:12:06,271 --> 00:12:08,448
His girlfriend's pretty well-known.
Her name is...

211
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:15,269
As far as I know,
she's not from the staff department.

212
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:16,950
I'll help you ask around
if I get a chance.

213
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,810
Thanks, I appreciate it.

214
00:12:22,890 --> 00:12:23,570
Ms. Wu,

215
00:12:23,570 --> 00:12:24,650
let me confirm

216
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:25,700
what you just

217
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:26,890
told me.

218
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:28,850
You signed up on a dating website,

219
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:30,960
and they matched you
with several people.

220
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:32,490
And you kept in touch

221
00:12:32,490 --> 00:12:33,760
with three of them.

222
00:12:34,570 --> 00:12:35,460
Yes.

223
00:12:35,970 --> 00:12:37,050
And out of the three,

224
00:12:37,050 --> 00:12:39,050
two scammed you

225
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,048
and then disappeared?

226
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:42,360
Yes, that's what happened.

227
00:12:43,770 --> 00:12:45,140
One didn't

228
00:12:45,290 --> 00:12:47,410
scam much.

229
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,740
But the other one was horrible...

230
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:50,920
Ms. Wu,

231
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:53,080
no need to be vague.

232
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,970
Can you give us their names
and phone numbers?

233
00:12:54,970 --> 00:12:56,493
We'll note them down and follow up.

234
00:12:56,890 --> 00:12:57,610
Well...

235
00:12:57,980 --> 00:12:59,230
The names were fake.

236
00:12:59,730 --> 00:13:01,760
The numbers are all out of service now.

237
00:13:02,330 --> 00:13:04,090
If I could find them myself,

238
00:13:04,190 --> 00:13:06,670
I wouldn't have come to you.

239
00:13:09,570 --> 00:13:10,570
How much did the one

240
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,530
who scammed you the most take

241
00:13:12,570 --> 00:13:13,520
from you?

242
00:13:14,610 --> 00:13:16,300
About 70,000 to 80,000 yuan.

243
00:13:16,810 --> 00:13:17,690
That's quite a bit.

244
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:19,270
Did you report it?

245
00:13:19,690 --> 00:13:20,320
I did.

246
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:22,200
The local station logged it,

247
00:13:22,730 --> 00:13:25,440
but they still haven't found him.

248
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:27,760
Can you give us a physical description

249
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:28,680
of the guy?

250
00:13:29,530 --> 00:13:30,870
He was tall

251
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:32,480
and slim.

252
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:34,280
Fair-skinned.

253
00:13:35,180 --> 00:13:36,200
Wore glasses.

254
00:13:36,804 --> 00:13:38,182
Looked gentle and polite.

255
00:13:38,410 --> 00:13:40,520
Didn't look like a scammer at all.

256
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:42,604
And he had the smoothest way of talking.

257
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:44,530
Who would've thought

258
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,830
he'd turn out to be so heartless?

259
00:13:47,330 --> 00:13:49,150
That's exactly how these people work.

260
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,890
They act all harmless

261
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,800
to target kind-hearted women like you.

262
00:13:54,810 --> 00:13:55,970
We've recorded everything.

263
00:13:56,010 --> 00:13:57,710
Why don't you head home for now?

264
00:13:58,090 --> 00:13:58,540
All right.

265
00:13:58,970 --> 00:13:59,860
Please make sure

266
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:01,790
to expose

267
00:14:01,790 --> 00:14:02,520
these fake daters.

268
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:05,000
So others don't get duped like I did.

269
00:14:06,370 --> 00:14:07,330
We will.

270
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:08,870
Thank you.

271
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:09,715
You can go back now.

272
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:11,120
I'll head out, then.

273
00:14:11,182 --> 00:14:12,071
This way, please.

274
00:14:18,370 --> 00:14:19,830
This one's tricky.

275
00:14:20,050 --> 00:14:21,700
I heard that site's

276
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:23,530
still running matchmaking events.

277
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,390
Maybe we should check it out
and try our luck?

278
00:14:25,737 --> 00:14:27,093
We could do a feature on this.

279
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:28,240
Hai.

280
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:29,940
Get the gear ready.

281
00:14:33,890 --> 00:14:35,880
This homestay isn't bad. It's pretty.

282
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:37,226
- Let's check it out.
- Come on.

283
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:40,160
Slow down.

284
00:15:01,010 --> 00:15:01,420
Done.

285
00:15:01,570 --> 00:15:01,980
Okay.

286
00:15:02,930 --> 00:15:03,530
Take a look.

287
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,850
There's a bird's nest over there!

288
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:05,850
Come on!

289
00:15:06,182 --> 00:15:07,710
Aren't you going to check the pictures?

290
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:08,350
Sure.

291
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,290
Later.

292
00:15:13,270 --> 00:15:14,940
I'm a bird!

293
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:27,470
Honey.

294
00:15:28,290 --> 00:15:28,610
Honey.

295
00:15:28,610 --> 00:15:29,580
Zong Qing!

296
00:15:30,050 --> 00:15:32,010
Why did you drop me?

297
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:33,610
Honey, I didn't mean to.

298
00:15:33,610 --> 00:15:35,048
I didn't expect you to be that heavy.

299
00:15:35,048 --> 00:15:35,604
Excuse me?

300
00:15:35,650 --> 00:15:36,810
I... I meant

301
00:15:36,810 --> 00:15:38,450
I didn't expect the thing
to be so flimsy.

302
00:15:39,582 --> 00:15:40,410
Where does it hurt?

303
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:42,880
My lower back.

304
00:15:43,170 --> 00:15:44,040
I'll rub it for you.

305
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:45,890
Help me up.

306
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:46,800
Okay.

307
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:52,920
You okay, Honey?

308
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:00,650
Come in.

309
00:16:01,570 --> 00:16:03,090
Room service.

310
00:16:04,810 --> 00:16:05,810
Dressed up so nicely

311
00:16:05,930 --> 00:16:07,090
on a weekend.

312
00:16:09,582 --> 00:16:11,330
You even did your eyebrows and eyeliner.

313
00:16:12,770 --> 00:16:14,170
You're all dolled up.

314
00:16:15,570 --> 00:16:17,050
What big event are you going to?

315
00:16:17,730 --> 00:16:18,900
Nothing major.

316
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:20,410
It's just a small event.

317
00:16:20,810 --> 00:16:21,810
What kind of event?

318
00:16:23,090 --> 00:16:24,470
Dad, can you not ask?

319
00:16:24,470 --> 00:16:25,370
I'm an adult.

320
00:16:25,370 --> 00:16:26,690
Can I not have a little privacy?

321
00:16:27,404 --> 00:16:29,737
You're not leaving the house
until you tell me.

322
00:16:32,570 --> 00:16:33,330
Fine.

323
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:38,910
Come here.

324
00:16:41,915 --> 00:16:43,050
I'm going on a blind date.

325
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:45,937
You've got to be kidding me.

326
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:46,680
Nope.

327
00:16:47,050 --> 00:16:47,610
Tang Xin,

328
00:16:47,610 --> 00:16:49,180
are you doing this just to spite me?

329
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:51,080
I introduced you

330
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,109
to a great guy like Wu Si

331
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:53,915
and you didn't even
give him a proper chance.

332
00:16:54,010 --> 00:16:55,493
And now you're going on a blind date?

333
00:16:55,515 --> 00:16:56,300
I refuse to believe

334
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,940
