335
00:16:58,090 --> 00:16:59,330
You never know.

336
00:17:03,782 --> 00:17:05,150
You're going to be the death of me!

337
00:17:24,730 --> 00:17:26,410
Finally, a bed! This feels amazing.

338
00:17:26,426 --> 00:17:27,720
- Feels good, right?
- So good.

339
00:17:27,970 --> 00:17:29,110
- Miss.
- Join me, Honey.

340
00:17:29,410 --> 00:17:30,770
Get up.

341
00:17:31,770 --> 00:17:32,770
Let's unpack first.

342
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:34,070
Whenever we arrive somewhere,

343
00:17:34,070 --> 00:17:36,050
we get in the habit
of unpacking right away. Got it?

344
00:17:41,782 --> 00:17:42,610
What do you think?

345
00:17:42,710 --> 00:17:44,220
Not a bad choice, right?

346
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:45,160
It's beautiful, huh?

347
00:17:45,293 --> 00:17:47,426
My wife picked this place.
Of course it's beautiful.

348
00:17:50,337 --> 00:17:51,430
I need to use the bathroom.

349
00:17:53,248 --> 00:17:54,250
This is a big room.

350
00:17:59,730 --> 00:18:00,380
Honey!

351
00:18:00,450 --> 00:18:01,570
What is it?

352
00:18:01,690 --> 00:18:02,700
Honey! Honey!

353
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:03,620
A bug!

354
00:18:03,820 --> 00:18:04,610
Where?

355
00:18:04,610 --> 00:18:05,820
Under the pillow!

356
00:18:06,610 --> 00:18:07,570
Wait. Don't go near it.

357
00:18:07,570 --> 00:18:08,660
It's fine. I'll take a look.

358
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:12,850
Where was it?

359
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,720
Right under that pillow!

360
00:18:14,915 --> 00:18:15,890
There's nothing here.

361
00:18:16,810 --> 00:18:17,850
There is!

362
00:18:17,915 --> 00:18:18,970
How big is the bug?

363
00:18:18,970 --> 00:18:20,610
This big.

364
00:18:21,050 --> 00:18:22,410
This big.

365
00:18:23,210 --> 00:18:24,010
How big exactly?

366
00:18:24,050 --> 00:18:25,030
This big!

367
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:26,250
Listen.

368
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:28,210
Back in survival training,

369
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:30,210
we had to eat bugs that size raw.

370
00:18:30,730 --> 00:18:31,890
That's gross.

371
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:34,650
You're not scared, but I am.

372
00:18:34,671 --> 00:18:37,490
Ever since I was a kid, the one thing
I've been terrified of is bugs.

373
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:39,570
Don't worry. Come sit.

374
00:18:39,670 --> 00:18:41,140
No way! What if it bites me?

375
00:18:41,450 --> 00:18:43,430
If it bites anyone,
it'll bite me first. Sit.

376
00:18:46,430 --> 00:18:47,250
Trust me.

377
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:49,440
Before you go to sleep tonight,

378
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:51,626
I promise
I'll eat every single bug in this place.

379
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:54,350
Honey,

380
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:56,050
maybe

381
00:18:56,810 --> 00:18:58,030
we should just go home.

382
00:19:16,782 --> 00:19:18,320
So much for an internet-famous homestay.

383
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:19,760
Many cockroaches and mosquitoes.

384
00:19:19,804 --> 00:19:20,960
Uh-huh. One-star.

385
00:19:21,290 --> 00:19:22,270
Home is still the best.

386
00:19:27,290 --> 00:19:28,170
And home has you,

387
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:29,910
my super handsome husband.

388
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:38,530
What is it?

389
00:19:46,970 --> 00:19:48,850
I might have to go back for training.

390
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:58,090
Honey?

391
00:20:02,050 --> 00:20:03,140
Princess?

392
00:20:05,930 --> 00:20:06,850
Don't be like that.

393
00:20:07,850 --> 00:20:09,010
Don't touch me.

394
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:10,620
What did I do?

395
00:20:11,290 --> 00:20:12,440
I'm not mad.

396
00:20:12,471 --> 00:20:13,582
Just go back to the unit.

397
00:20:17,130 --> 00:20:17,610
Okay.

398
00:20:19,315 --> 00:20:21,271
I'll call the base
and request leave right now.

399
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:22,290
I'll skip the training.

400
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:23,160
What are you doing?

401
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,810
You can't just skip training.

402
00:20:24,810 --> 00:20:27,093
If my dad finds out, he'll say
I'm being irresponsible again.

403
00:20:28,010 --> 00:20:29,530
I knew my Yangyang was the best.

404
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:30,930
You'll understand me, right?

405
00:20:30,930 --> 00:20:31,850
You owe me big time,

406
00:20:32,090 --> 00:20:33,740
you know that?

407
00:20:34,170 --> 00:20:36,490
Honeymoon, trips, movies,

408
00:20:36,930 --> 00:20:38,990
snacks, and a camping trip.

409
00:20:43,530 --> 00:20:44,740
I've got three hours left

410
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:46,160
before I have to head back to base.

411
00:20:46,226 --> 00:20:47,404
Subtract travel time,

412
00:20:48,770 --> 00:20:49,900
and that leaves us two hours.

413
00:20:53,970 --> 00:20:55,090
What do you want to do

414
00:20:55,370 --> 00:20:56,250
with those two hours?

415
00:20:56,810 --> 00:20:58,010
We have two hours.

416
00:21:00,730 --> 00:21:03,115
I want to take you camping. Right now.

417
00:21:07,650 --> 00:21:08,410
Thanks.

418
00:21:35,290 --> 00:21:36,640
Hey, can I get to know you?

419
00:21:36,826 --> 00:21:38,090
Sorry, I'm here to meet someone.

420
00:21:38,090 --> 00:21:39,350
We can add each other on WeChat?

421
00:21:39,350 --> 00:21:40,130
I won't bother you.

422
00:21:40,130 --> 00:21:41,650
I'm not comfortable adding strangers.

423
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:43,515
Maybe we can follow each other on Weibo?

424
00:21:43,610 --> 00:21:45,170
I don't have a Weibo account.

425
00:21:45,410 --> 00:21:46,130
Sorry.

426
00:22:14,970 --> 00:22:15,860
Honey!

427
00:22:16,130 --> 00:22:16,740
Do you like it?

428
00:22:16,970 --> 00:22:19,680
I love it! This is so romantic.

429
00:22:19,810 --> 00:22:20,780
Come on. Let's go inside.

430
00:22:27,490 --> 00:22:29,040
How did you set all this up?

431
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:35,160
And all these snacks!

432
00:22:36,490 --> 00:22:37,590
They're all your favorites.

433
00:22:50,370 --> 00:22:51,090
Young man.

434
00:22:51,970 --> 00:22:53,250
Can I call you that?

435
00:22:53,730 --> 00:22:55,290
I'm probably a few years older than you.

436
00:22:57,290 --> 00:22:58,560
I'm not here for a date.

437
00:22:59,010 --> 00:22:59,980
I'm looking for someone.

438
00:23:01,410 --> 00:23:03,090
Everyone here is looking for someone.

439
00:23:03,090 --> 00:23:04,300
Let's have a quick chat.

440
00:23:04,530 --> 00:23:05,370
You probably

441
00:23:05,370 --> 00:23:07,110
just graduated not long ago, right?

442
00:23:07,330 --> 00:23:08,150
In your early 20s?

443
00:23:10,970 --> 00:23:11,810
My last name's Li.

444
00:23:12,370 --> 00:23:13,850
I started my own business years ago.

445
00:23:13,970 --> 00:23:15,890
I've got a few small companies now,

446
00:23:15,890 --> 00:23:17,640
plus some online platforms.

447
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:18,770
They're doing decently.

448
00:23:19,410 --> 00:23:20,090
Can I ask

449
00:23:20,090 --> 00:23:21,410
what you do?

450
00:23:24,871 --> 00:23:26,448
I'm a member of the military.

451
00:23:26,570 --> 00:23:27,290
The military?

452
00:23:29,490 --> 00:23:30,750
What's the point

453
00:23:30,750 --> 00:23:32,382
of joining the military
in today's world?

454
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:33,330
I heard

455
00:23:33,330 --> 00:23:34,770
training is brutal,

456
00:23:35,010 --> 00:23:36,370
and you hardly get to go home.

457
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:37,040
Ma'am,

458
00:23:37,582 --> 00:23:39,271
if you don't understand the military,

459
00:23:39,650 --> 00:23:40,930
please don't speak on it.

460
00:23:43,370 --> 00:23:44,970
I may not know the military,

461
00:23:45,290 --> 00:23:46,610
but I sure know society.

462
00:23:46,690 --> 00:23:48,370
Without a solid financial foundation,

463
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:49,730
you're not going to make it far.

464
00:23:50,130 --> 00:23:51,450
I've seen plenty of guys

465
00:23:51,490 --> 00:23:52,730
like you.

466
00:23:54,250 --> 00:23:55,450
Why'd you join the military?

467
00:23:58,770 --> 00:24:00,610
You look sharp.

468
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:02,250
Don't you want to get rich?

469
00:24:04,850 --> 00:24:05,970
I'm just kidding.

470
00:24:10,730 --> 00:24:11,380
Honey.

471
00:24:13,130 --> 00:24:15,330
Are we just going to spend
this precious hour

472
00:24:17,130 --> 00:24:18,140
snacking?

473
00:24:19,537 --> 00:24:20,737
What else do you want to do?

474
00:24:25,210 --> 00:24:25,930
Look at me.

475
00:24:33,290 --> 00:24:33,870
Hold on.

476
00:24:35,130 --> 00:24:36,050
Honey,

477
00:24:38,770 --> 00:24:40,250
your skin is way too rough.

478
00:24:42,490 --> 00:24:43,400
Close your eyes.

479
00:24:47,650 --> 00:24:49,070
All set, Honey. Come at me.

480
00:24:56,130 --> 00:24:57,050
Cold! Cold! Cold!

481
00:24:57,050 --> 00:24:58,570
- Don't move.
- Cold!

482
00:24:58,610 --> 00:24:59,826
- Cold...
- Stay still.

483
00:25:02,730 --> 00:25:04,970
This is an emergency mask.

484
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:06,770
It hydrates, moisturizes,

485
00:25:06,770 --> 00:25:08,380
and soothes the skin.

486
00:25:08,570 --> 00:25:09,540
Your face

487
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:10,780
is cracking from dryness.

488
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,450
If you don't start taking care of it,

489
00:25:12,671 --> 00:25:14,315
I might not want you anymore.

490
00:25:15,250 --> 00:25:16,090
In my unit,

491
00:25:16,090 --> 00:25:17,610
I'm known for having baby-soft skin.

492
00:25:17,890 --> 00:25:19,030
The others are much worse.

493
00:25:19,030 --> 00:25:20,900
Nobody says they're unwanted.

494
00:25:21,810 --> 00:25:22,670
Even better.

495
00:25:22,810 --> 00:25:24,530
Take all these masks back with you.

496
00:25:24,530 --> 00:25:25,730
Use them together.

497
00:25:25,730 --> 00:25:26,730
Especially your captain.

498
00:25:26,770 --> 00:25:28,730
His skin needs serious help.

499
00:25:29,050 --> 00:25:30,590
He won't win over Xin, otherwise.

500
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:31,490
Well,

501
00:25:31,490 --> 00:25:33,370
I'm curious about your plans.

502
00:25:34,450 --> 00:25:36,570
These days young people
are all chasing money.

503
00:25:36,650 --> 00:25:38,420
Why are you toughing it out
in the military?

504
00:25:38,420 --> 00:25:39,530
What do you get out of it?

505
00:25:44,671 --> 00:25:45,780
I know at least one benefit.

506
00:25:48,130 --> 00:25:49,220
I don't have

507
00:25:49,730 --> 00:25:50,780
to talk to you.

508
00:25:59,850 --> 00:26:02,290
Oh, come on.

509
00:26:02,490 --> 00:26:03,780
When I was your age,

510
00:26:03,780 --> 00:26:05,410
I was already out hustling.

511
00:26:05,930 --> 00:26:07,020
Everyone starts off

512
00:26:07,570 --> 00:26:09,140
with dreams and ambitions.

513
00:26:09,730 --> 00:26:11,600
Then reality hits, and you grow up.

514
00:26:12,330 --> 00:26:13,450
With your looks, you'd have

515
00:26:13,450 --> 00:26:14,570
no problem finding someone

516
00:26:14,570 --> 00:26:15,826
if you weren't in the military.

517
00:26:16,050 --> 00:26:18,070
But hey, you chose this,

518
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:20,310
so don't be surprised
if people are a bit picky.

519
00:26:21,050 --> 00:26:22,130
It's fine for men

520
00:26:22,230 --> 00:26:24,770
to be poor when they're young.

521
00:26:25,330 --> 00:26:26,680
We're both adults here.

522
00:26:26,810 --> 00:26:28,530
I'll cut to the chase.

523
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:30,610
I like your vibe.

524
00:26:30,610 --> 00:26:31,530
I'm interested.

525
00:26:31,530 --> 00:26:32,740
I want to get to know you.

526
00:26:32,890 --> 00:26:35,170
They say it's better to marry well
than to be raised well.

527
00:26:35,380 --> 00:26:36,330
But for men,

528
00:26:36,330 --> 00:26:37,915
marrying well is even more important.

529
00:26:38,370 --> 00:26:39,810
I'm 35.

530
00:26:39,810 --> 00:26:40,870
Divorced.

531
00:26:41,010 --> 00:26:41,890
Childfree.

532
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:43,690
Started my business young,

533
00:26:43,970 --> 00:26:46,410
now financially free.

534
00:26:47,770 --> 00:26:49,160
From the moment I saw you,

535
00:26:49,570 --> 00:26:50,630
I liked you.

536
00:26:52,570 --> 00:26:54,570
I doubt you get paid much.

537
00:26:54,730 --> 00:26:56,050
So, how about you come be with me?

538
00:26:56,690 --> 00:26:58,780
It's better than wasting away
in the military.

539
00:26:59,290 --> 00:27:01,230
Even if we break up later,

540
00:27:01,370 --> 00:27:02,850
you can always go back to it.

541
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:04,490
We taxpayers

542
00:27:04,850 --> 00:27:06,250
are still footing your salary.

543
00:27:07,130 --> 00:27:09,290
Wow. You really know how to talk.

544
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,460
Never in my life have I met someone

545
00:27:12,460 --> 00:27:14,450
who's so good at making a point.

546
00:27:15,204 --> 00:27:16,493
But perhaps you've never heard

547
00:27:16,493 --> 00:27:18,170
of the Law on the Protection
of the Status and Rights

548
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:19,810
and Interests
of Military Personnel of China?

549
00:27:19,810 --> 00:27:21,530
A soldier's honor and reputation

550
00:27:21,530 --> 00:27:22,970
are protected by law.

551
00:27:23,370 --> 00:27:24,960
No organization or individual is allowed

552
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,610
to slander or diminish

553
00:27:26,610 --> 00:27:29,140
a soldier's dignity in any form.

554
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:32,610
We were having a conversation.

555
00:27:32,610 --> 00:27:34,120
What's it got to do with you?

556
00:27:34,650 --> 00:27:36,770
I'm a single woman here

557
00:27:36,770 --> 00:27:39,850
for the matchmaking too.

558
00:27:40,210 --> 00:27:41,690
But hearing you try

559
00:27:41,690 --> 00:27:43,540
to "poach" someone from the military?

560
00:27:43,540 --> 00:27:44,100
It absolutely

561
00:27:45,050 --> 00:27:46,130
blew my mind.

562
00:27:46,448 --> 00:27:47,190
What's it to you?

563
00:27:48,050 --> 00:27:49,410
The military owes you or something?

564
00:27:50,115 --> 00:27:52,960
If it weren't for people like him
toughing it out in the military,

565
00:27:53,330 --> 00:27:55,040
you wouldn't even be here

566
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:57,050
enjoying the freedom to judge and pick.

567
00:27:59,100 --> 00:28:00,740
Fine.

568
00:28:00,890 --> 00:28:02,590
You can have my seat.

569
00:28:02,810 --> 00:28:03,210
Whatever.

